<|startoftext|>Dish: konabari soup  with tahini sauce by alton brown
Directions: using one large pot , place the chicken pieces in pot
over medium heat with canola oil , saute the chicken until lightly browned
remove the chicken and set aside
add a large saute pan or griddle or large pan to moderate the heat of the saute pan and then add the onion and garlic
cook until soft
add the mushrooms and continue to cook until the mushrooms begin to soften
add the garlic and continue to cook until the mushrooms are lightly brown
add the cayenne pepper strips and cook 1 minute
add broth to the mushroom mixture and bring to a boil
add the tahini paste , return to a low heat and return the chicken pieces and the mushroom mixture to simmer , covering the pot when you turn the heat down for 15-20 minutes
remove the cayenne and garlic cloves from the pot and add them to the pot , along with a 1 / 4 cup of the tahini / broth mixture
heat until the chicken cubes are warmed through , about 20 minutes
do not overcook or the tahini will cause the water to reduce too much and the broth to curdle
serve with a selection of sliced veggies of your choice if desired
garnish with chopped cilantro and mint
enjoy with fresh , warm bread and a salad
